<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName>,
                                    Second Assistant Secretary of State, to Mr. <persName type="to">Field</persName>, Acting Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                        State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-08-20"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 20,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: In view of the doubt which may
                                yet remain in the case of the Hornet, from the fact stated in the
                                inclosed communications of the <pb facs="0852" n="838" xml:id="pg_838"/> 19th instant from Marshal Barlow, I prefer not
                                to take the responsibility of advising her release in advance of the
                                arrival of Mr. Davis, who is expected to return tonight.</p>
                            <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>W. HUNTER,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Second Assistant
                                        Secretary.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. A. Field</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Attorney-General.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>